#* {{quote-journal |en |journal=Oceanus |volume=12 |year=1965 |publisher=[[w:Woods Hole Oceanographic Institution|Woods Hole Oceanographic Institution]] |text=In the meantime suspended underwater cameras and deep submersibles, both the bathyscaphs ‘Trieste’ and ‘Archimede’ and the '''soucoupe''' of Cousteau have been employed extensively in attempts to identify various scattering layers.}}
